migrations/ @jrmatherly

# Security-sensitive paths (SOC 2 CC8.1: change management).
# These declarations tell GitHub which paths are under the auth/audit/
# secrets-handling policy. Branch-protection rules in GitHub settings
# enforce the required-reviewer count (currently 1 in single-maintainer
# mode; flip to 2 once a security team handle is added below).
#
# To bring a real security team online: replace @jrmatherly on the
# entries below with @spacebot-security-team (or whichever handle is
# created), then update branch protection to require both
# `code-owners` and a minimum of 2 approvals on these paths.
/src/api/server.rs   @jrmatherly
/src/api/admin_*.rs  @jrmatherly
/src/auth/           @jrmatherly
/src/audit/          @jrmatherly
/src/secrets/        @jrmatherly
/src/admin.rs        @jrmatherly
/migrations/global/  @jrmatherly
/docs/security/      @jrmatherly
/docs/runbooks/      @jrmatherly
